Reasoning: The paper analyzes the distribution of attention given to competing organizations in the online environment, using large-scale longitudinal studies. This involves the use of social media datasets and the quantification of online attention received by organizations. The paper touches on topics such as preferential attachment, increasing returns, and global trade, which are relevant to the fields of social informatics (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), system and control (cs.SD), computational complexity (cs.CC), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
